# Respond to each piece of feedback (CI and reviews)

Assistants (**Cursor**, **Codex**, **Claude / Claude Code**) must treat automated and human review signals as requiring **explicit closure**, not silent dismissal.

Works with **`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`** and **`multiagent-modularity.mdc`** (watch checks; merge only when intended).

**Merge-ready:** implement **`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`** (**wait gate** ‚Üí enumerate ‚Üí judge ‚Üí **in-thread** reply: implemented/deferred/declined ‚Üí merge / first-time auto-merge).

## What counts as feedback

- **Failures** from required workflows (tests, lint, **`ci_result`**, etc.).
- **Inline comments** and **reviews** from humans.
- **Bot / integration comments** such as **`sourcery-ai`** / **`gemini-code-assist`** / **`coderabbit`** / **`copilot`**, **`chatgpt-codex-connector`**, or similar on the opened PR‚Äîor **email / notification summaries** that map to findings on **the same branch the assistant owns**.

## Mandatory behaviour (each distinct finding)

1. **Enumerate** ‚Äî distinct failing jobs, logs, review threads (merge truly duplicate verbatim threads into **one** reply that references both locations).
2. **Judge merits** against project rules and scope (**real-data-only tests**, **data-first UI**, modular files, scope of task). Prefer implementing good fixes; politely decline incorrect or out-of-scope items with a substantive reason‚Äînot silence.
3. **Respond directly** on GitHub (**preferred**):
   - **Accepted:** follow-up commits on the same branch **and/or** reply that the suggestion is addressed in commit `<sha>`.
   - **Declined or deferred:** reply on the thread with a concrete reason (out of scope, conflicts with **`AGENTS.md`**, backlog link, behavioural requirement, etc.).
4. Treat the branch as merge-ready **only after** substantive feedback threads are closed‚Äînot left hanging because a check stayed green while a bot commented.

## When GitHub inline replies are unavailable

Append **`## Feedback responses`** to the PR body‚Äîor the closing push summary‚Äîlisting each item: source/tool (optional), file/topic, **done / skipped + why**, SHA if applicable.

## Do not

- Claim there is **no actionable bot feedback** from a **single top-level review comment** without checking **all** inline threads for that bot (**`chatgpt-codex-connector`**, **`gemini-code-assist`**, etc.). Top-level text can be generic while file comments carry P1/P2 items.
- Dismiss **`sourcery`**, **`gemini-code-assist`**, or similar as ‚Äúnon-blocking third-party noise‚Äù **without** per-item resolution (code + thread **or** written decline reason).
- Merge or finalize a PR the assistant owns when **identified** automated or human review comments remain unaddressed and unstated why.

## Relation to failing CI

- **Required failing checks**: fix-forward until green (existing **`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`**).
- **Bots that comment while checks succeed**: apply this document‚Äôs enumerate / judge / respond loop; passing CI **does not** waive thread closure.
